        "setup": "Start a Dagger session with the [Dagger CLI installation guide](https://docs.dagger.io/getting-started/installation/). The CLI exposes a per-session local API and provides the token in the `DAGGER_SESSION_TOKEN` environment variable; docs show using `dagger run ...` for ephemeral sessions or setting `DAGGER_SESSION_TOKEN` yourself before `dagger listen --allow-cors` to run a local GraphQL server. Use the token as the HTTP Basic username with an empty password (or `token:` before Base64 encoding). See [Using the Dagger API with HTTP and GraphQL](https://docs.dagger.io/getting-started/api/http/) and [GraphQL Playground](https://docs.dagger.io/extending/api-playground).",
